<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,1558,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,445,1799,1825]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Etymology</emphasis>
. — The species epithet, “ 
<taxonomicName box="[746,878,1799,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Corduliidae" genus="Lauromacromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picinguaba">
<emphasis box="[746,878,1799,1824]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">picinguaba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, refers to the type­locality. It is a latinized word from the Tupi­Guarani (a Brazilian indigenous language) that means “refuge of fishes”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
